column5: has anyone fished Boois Joyce lake outpost? any info would be helpful

I have not fished it but discussed the option with Jim Booi. Its said to be a good pike lake up to 44" but an average fly-in walleye lake. The lake gets minimal pressure as I don't think thecamp is utilized much.

Jim said last week that Joyce Lake has hardly been used this year at all. There was a gentleman at Trout Lake camp named Jeff that was a regular at Boois who was telling me about Joyce Lake and he said fishing is good, cabin rustic. A fisherman's camp.

Joyce Lake outpost under new ownership ... new docks , NEW larger cabin available July 2016 This lake is under utilized with numerous 40" + northerns and walleye til you are tired of catching them See facebook page Wildeyes Wilderness Escape for pics and more info
Good to know, thanks! Having researched Joyce I'm well aware it's a good fishery. It was already on my hit list but just moved a few notches closer to the top.
who owns the outpost now?id like to contact them
thanks for the info,good price!i didnt know it was a 20 hour drive though
